1
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:46,920
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL <i>DEEP AFFECTION EYES</i>
BY ER DONG TU ZI ON JJWXC.NET

2
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:57,440
Don't you feel like everything's spinning?
My head won't stop reeling.

3
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:00,600
It's like the whole place is tilting.

4
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,519
Can you slow down a little?

5
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:09,240
You're pretty quick on your feet.

6
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:12,920
Wait, are you drunk?
Your face is burning red.

7
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,600
You're the one who's drunk.
Look at yourself.

8
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,400
What's the room number?

9
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,240
We're already here.

10
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,800
Li Jinyu…

11
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:37,240
You've got eyes of deep affection.

12
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:39,360
They're really beautiful.

13
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,840
Enough. Go inside.

14
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,920
Okay. Let me find the keycard.

15
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,360
What's wrong? Lost your nerve?

16
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,040
Stop it.

17
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,240
You're drunk.

18
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,360
Just go in.

19
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,120
Serves you right.

20
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,400
Why drink like that
when you can't hold it?

21
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:41,920
I just need a minute.

22
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,720
Don't leave me.

23
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,880
I'm too tired tonight.

24
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,640
Let's save it for another time.

25
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:32,920
Uncle Yang?

26
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,920
Jinyu?

27
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,560
Here, have some water.

28
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,720
What brings you here?

29
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:52,200
Earlier this evening,

30
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:55,160
Ye Meng texted me. She sounded worried.

31
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,600
Asked me to come check on a friend.

32
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:01,120
And how do you two know each other?

33
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,760
That's a long story.

34
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,640
A few years back,

35
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,640
our counseling center

36
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,440
came to Ningsui to give some public talks.

37
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,920
Back then, people in this town
were so closed off,

38
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,960
no one showed up.

39
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,560
Except Ye Meng. She came every time,

40
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,920
asking endless questions about depression.

41
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,280
So, she knows about your past?

42
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,600
No.

43
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,640
She just can't help herself.
Always rushing in to help.

44
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,040
You couldn't stop her if you tried.

45
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:32,480
I remember before you moved here,

46
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,480
you were popular among girls.

47
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,560
You just never dated.

48
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:38,280
That's why I told you back then,
try it at least once.

49
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,960
Oh, and just recently,

50
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,360
your grandma mentioned

51
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,320
you'd met a girl from Jiangbei.

52
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,400
I never imagined it would be Meng.

53
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:48,120
It wasn't her.

54
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,520
That wasn't dating,
just a blind date Grandma set up.

55
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,200
We only met once.

56
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,160
Either way, you seem better now.

57
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,320
What happened in the past
wasn't your fault.

58
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,200
Stop punishing yourself for it.

59
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,320
As long

60
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,040
as nobody brings her up,

61
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,360
I'm fine.

62
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:09,800
Jinyu, you ever hear
of the white bear phenomenon?

63
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,720
The thing is, the harder you try

64
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,880
not to think about something,

65
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,920
the more it stays on your mind.

66
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:18,680
I understand it's not easy
to put the past behind you.

67
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:21,320
But don't rush it.
And don't run from it either.

68
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Alright. If there's nothing else,
I'll get going.

69
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,760
Let me walk you out, Uncle Yang.

70
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,120
No need.

71
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:32,000
And listen, if you don't
want her to know your past,

72
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,880
I'll act like we never met.

73
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,920
Safe trip home, Uncle Yang.

74
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,800
<i>Li Jinyu.</i>

75
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,800
Li Jinyu.

76
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,560
Li Jinyu…

77
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,680
I'm thirsty.

78
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,360
Thanks.

79
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:44,720
Looking for Uncle Yang?

80
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,320
He already left.

81
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,080
How was the talk?

82
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,400
He's been my therapist all along.

83
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,680
I've been seeing him for years.

84
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,640
But you…

85
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,840
What are you doing
sitting in on counseling?

86
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,400
Grandma told me my mom had depression.

87
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,000
I just couldn't believe it.

88
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,560
She was always so full of life.

89
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,200
How could she be depressed?

90
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,720
So, I went to every one
of Uncle Yang's lectures.

91
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,920
Li Jinyu,

92
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:31,560
I know you think I butt into everything.

93
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,120
But I really am afraid you'll…

94
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,640
Forget it.

95
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:42,960
What I'm really trying to say

96
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,960
is I hope you can let people in.

97
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,280
I've just gotten used

98
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,560
to being on my own.

99
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,360
It feels like I went through

100
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,360
all the hardest parts of my life

101
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,560
all by myself.

102
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Not anymore. You've got me.

103
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,600
Look at me.

104
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,920
I'm steady, successful,
plenty of time on my hands.

105
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,840
Don't you want to consider it?

106
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,040
So, what is it you like about me?

107
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,440
That face alone is enough.

108
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:28,040
It's the first time in my life
I ever asked a guy for his WeChat.

109
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:32,080
Didn't you tell me you only wanted
my contact for that crab place?

110
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,640
Don't pretend you believed that.

111
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,160
You'd better not play games with me.

112
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,880
When I fall for someone,

113
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,120
I don't change.

114
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,080
Funny.

115
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,680
I'm the same way.

116
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,560
That's still up for debate.

117
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,400
If I'd known, I wouldn't
have asked Uncle Yang to come.

118
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,920
I'd have just gone after you myself.

119
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,040
Let's see how smug you'd be.

120
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,360
Who's the smug one here?

121
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:03,720
You should be grateful
I didn't take advantage tonight.

122
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,200
Oh, please. As if you'd dare.

123
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,800
Is that a challenge?

124
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,680
Good thing the night's still young.

125
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,560
If I wanted to make a move,

126
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,000
I'd have plenty of time.

127
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,040
Do whatever you want.

128
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,960
It's not like I'd be the one losing.

129
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,280
SLEEP MODE

130
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,480
Good night.

131
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,760
Such a gentleman.

132
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,360
I've been looking for you all night.

133
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,240
So, this is where you've been.

134
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,120
You're with Ye Meng now?

135
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:33,320
Does knowing the answer

136
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,160
matter that much to you?

137
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:39,360
You don't like me.
When you acted like you did,

138
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,640
it was just to provoke her.

139
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,240
You hate her that much?

140
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:45,400
Hate is putting it lightly.

141
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:48,560
All through school,
everyone preferred her.

142
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,280
Every boy I liked ended up liking her.

143
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:53,200
Even my parents never stopped saying,

144
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,600
"Why can't you be like Ye Meng?

145
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:56,640
She's beautiful. She's sweet."

146
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,640
And what about me? I've got charm too.

147
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,960
I'm not bad-looking, right?

148
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,520
And my grades left hers in the dust.

149
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,640
So, why is she the one
everyone calls the perfect daughter?

150
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,040
Maybe in her eyes, you were the one

151
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,000
people compared her to.

152
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,440
Even if that's true,

153
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,120
there's no way I'll ever sit down

154
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,840
and share a meal with her.

155
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:24,080
We'll probably resent each other
for the rest of our lives.

156
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,160
Sorry.

157
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:30,360
I used you as a pawn again.

158
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:32,680
But I hope we can still be friends.

159
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:37,440
And if you really do care about Ye Meng,

160
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,120
then take my advice.

161
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,720
Keep her here in Ningsui.

162
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,360
Don't let her go back to Jiangbei.

163
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:56,000
BED 13

164
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,080
IMMUNIZATION STATION

165
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,720
- Jinyu, you're here.
- Hm.

166
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:04,360
PATIENT ROOM 5

167
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,960
Give it here.

168
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,960
Slash it once.

169
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,240
I need to tell you something.

170
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:30,480
I'm planning a trip to Jiangbei.

171
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,960
Jiangbei?

172
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:34,120
What for?

173
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,400
To see Li Lingbai.

174
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,000
You're going to that woman.

175
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,240
Have you completely lost your mind?

176
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:46,960
The ticket's already bought.

177
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,960
What nonsense is this?

178
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,960
I heard she's seriously ill.

179
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,360
Might not have much time left. As her son,

180
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,760
I have to show up and fight
for my share of the inheritance.

181
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,240
When I come back, I'll look after you.

182
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,280
We'll eat well, drink well.

183
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:06,600
Didn't you want to try
racing and skydiving, like me?

184
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,000
We'll take that world map,

185
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,920
throw a dart at it,

186
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,840
and fly wherever it lands.

187
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,120
I don't need her money.
I have plenty of my own.

188
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,160
And wipe that grin off your face.

189
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:23,880
You know exactly
what kind of person she is.

190
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,240
Fine.

191
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,640
If you insist, I won't stop you.

192
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,240
Call me the moment you land.

193
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,760
I already bought you sky-high insurance.

194
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,720
If anything happens,

195
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,440
at least I'll know where to collect.

196
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,880
Happy Spring Festival.

197
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,600
Don't even think about it.

198
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,560
Before the holiday,
I'll crawl back if I have to.

199
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,480
Now eat.

200
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:55,320
OPEN
WELCOME

201
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,920
<i>Pour in a little oil.</i>

202
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:01,800
<i>Then add 125 milliliters of milk.</i>

203
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:06,200
<i>Mix it well.</i>

204
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:09,960
<i>Now we can add the flour.</i>

205
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,360
You really don't sit still, do you?

206
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:15,120
Your leg just healed, and you're
already this busy. Don't overdo it.

207
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,040
Just film it properly.
It's Jiayu's school project.

208
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,040
They want a vlog.

209
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:21,320
It's the power of love. Get it?

210
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,000
Alright, alright. Forty-five degrees.
Makes your face look slimmer.

211
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:26,320
- Perfect.
- You got it? Let me see.

212
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,760
Here, check it.

213
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:31,200
- Well?
- Gorgeous. Absolutely perfect.

214
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,400
So, last night you two had drinks,

215
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:39,200
went back to the room,
and nothing happened?

216
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:42,280
That doesn't sound like
city dating etiquette to me.

217
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,520
I'm all about true love.

218
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,440
Please. You two are slower than slow.

219
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,960
A girl chasing a guy is easy.

220
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,640
But with you two?

221
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,440
It's like moving mountains.

222
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,440
So, tell me. Are your hints too weak,

223
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,600
or is he just pretending not to see them?

224
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:59,680
Because if it's the second one,
he's really pushing his luck.

225
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,360
Honestly, last night,
I wasn't even planning anything.

226
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,960
Then why'd you bring him to your room?

227
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,400
You wouldn't understand.

228
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,320
Oh, you're serious about him.

229
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,680
Stop it.

230
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:19,960
Okay, okay.

231
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,680
You're doomed, Ye Meng. Totally gone.

232
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,560
Head over heels.

233
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,200
- It's snowing.
- Where?

234
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,160
No way.

235
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,640
I'm not kidding. Come on. Hurry!

236
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,200
Careful with your leg.

237
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,720
I can't believe it's snowing in Ningsui.

238
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,360
I have to get this on video.

239
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,000
You asked me just now

240
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,520
if I was really serious about him.

241
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,920
Honestly, I don't know.

242
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,400
But my first instinct right now

243
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,560
isn't to take a photo for Moments.

244
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,800
Then, what is it?

245
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:08,640
I'm worried Li Jinyu
might not have an umbrella.

246
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,520
<i>Or that the streets are icy,</i>

247
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,119
<i>and he'll slip and fall.</i>

248
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,480
You sound like you're in a drama yourself.

249
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,040
YA'EN

250
